<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-849-394  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 849 394.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Oct 30 1989 v8 n22 p27(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Commtech offers 3-way software. (Commtech International Inc.'sXChange software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Olsen, Florence.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Commtech International Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   XCHANGE (Computer program) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Commtech Offers 3-Way SoftwareandM;Commtech International Inc. has bundled three communications applicationsinto the latest version of its PC software product, XChange.andM;One federal manager with the Postal Service said he recently bought thepackage, with the idea that it would help in collecting &quot;a lot of that littlenit-picky stuff down at our level that someone [higher up] is looking to getsummarized.&quot;andM;A field division logistics manager with the Postal Service, Dean Sleevi saidhe is evaluating the product to use as a telecommunications backbone for theequipment inventory data and budget information his division routinely mustcollect and forward upward in the Postal Service hierarchy.andM;Commtech officials said the Xchange package integrates PC remote-control,direct-connect and terminal mode communications.andM;XChange lets users schedule unattended file transfers overnight when phonerates are lowest.andM;Sleevi said another use is on-screen remote support.andM;&quot;If you are working on linear regressions in Lotus 2.01, it's possible foryou to call up [with XChange] and for me to show you exactly how thoseformulas and derivatives can be done,&quot; he said.andM;Until Nov. 1, the XChange package will sell for $145, Commtech officialssaid.andP;  After that, the price will be $245.andM;Contact Matt Thompson at Commtech International, tel.andP;  800-678-8988.andO;</TEXT></DOC>